postcontent: M9A3 semiauto pistol, Beretta has created a coming-together of all the tactical and functional features that today’s combat professionals may require.From Vertec-style thin grip to universal slide design convertible from safety-decocker to decocker-only, from a beveled magazine well to oversize mag-release button, from a 3-slot built-in Picatinny rail to high-capacity capability for maximum firepower.The Vertec-style vertical grip of the M9A3 offers two very important benefits. Its vertical configuration makes it easy to point the handgun to where one would normally point the index finger of the dominant hand. This instinctive pointing is highly prized by tactical shooters and makes for consistent--and consistently-accurate--target acquisition. Also, the grips are thin in spite of being able to accommodate a double-stack, high-capacity magazine. This makes trigger-reach simple even for those with smaller hands, besides offering a more compact profile for those carrying the M9A3 concealed. All this, plus the crisp checkering on the front- and backstrap as well as removable wraparound grip, make any combat hold simple and consistent.One of the most salient benefits of the M9A3 is its universal slide, which is easily convertible from FS to G mode. This means that the M9A3s safety lever can be used in a safety-decocker mode or it can be converted to perform a decocker-only function for those who prefer this configuration. More versatility is also offered in the form of a removable front sight, for tactical shooters who have a distinct preference in terms of sight picture, material or construction. In addition, a variety of accessorization options is possible thanks to the built-in 3-slot Picatinny rail located in front of the trigger guard, which enables the easy attachment of a variety of tactical lights, laser devices and more. Beretta has put a generous bevel at the magazine well, so that tactical magazine changes may be performed quickly and easily with one hand, regardless of lighting conditions. Along the same lines, the magazine-release button is oversized, making it simple to use when seconds count even while wearing gloves. And the M9A3 is low-maintenance thanks to its hyper-resistant FDE finish that is practically impervious to the elements, sand-resistant magazines in 15 or 17 rounds (10-round standard), and intuitive tool-free disassembly.

title: For Sale:  Conceal Carry/ Defensive/Tactical Pistol Instruction
postcontent: TriggerFarm® Firearms Training and Range provides Top Notch Firearms Instruction for the IL Concealed Carry and Defensive Pistol/Tactical instruction to further your Handgun Skills. Our instructors are Top Notch, they all come from Police/Law Enforcement/Military backgrounds, they have real world experience and a Professional Demenor for instruction. They do not portray the Drill Instructor Attitude. We pride ourselves in training beginners and shooters with limited experience drawing from a holster and shooting and or shooting while moving or from cover and concealment. More than likely a sense of humor will entail the seriousness of combat shooting, we know its a serious matter and we know how to push you to your limits of shooting under stress all in a very safe and enjoyable manner. We offer one Concealed Carry Class each Month, next one is May 5th and 6th 2018. The cost is $200.00 no hidden fees and no extra charge to use the Range cause we own and operate it. Check out our Website for additonal Dates for the Concealed Carry Classes and for updates on the renewal process staring this Fall.  Google TriggerFarm Firearms and it should appear. We also offer two Defensive Pistol Classes. A Basic and an Advanced.  In order to take the Advanced Class you must attend two of the Basic classes first, trust me you won't mind,  it will be fun and informative. Our classes mirror the standards set by Police and Military Professionals.  The cost for the Basic Defensive Pistol is only $50.00. For the Basic Class May 26th 2018 you will need to bring the following,  around 300 rounds of ammo, yes we actually shoot during the class,  a good functioning outside the waistband strong side holster, something that has decent retention and allows for a smooth draw and reholster. A reputable handgun that functions, this always gets a little tricky, it doesn't necessarly have to be the concealed carry pistol you tote around. The basic muscle memory and steps of drawing from a holster can be incorporated into different types of firearm and holster postions. Lets face it most of us change up holster positions and firearms at some point maybe depending on weather or types of clothes being wore, but the draw sequence and proceedure should be the same. For the purposes of the class Mid to Full size firearms work better, they hold more rounds therefore your not constantly reloading magazines but you decide what you wanna use if its something smaller, lower capacity just bring more magazines I would suggest 5 minimal for those firearms holding 10 or less and 3 for those that hold 10 or more. Magazine pouches are nice and allow for quick access and proper alingment for quick reloads, but they are not neccessary, pockets will work.  The class framework is as follows, Start out with a safety brief and review of the shooting fundementals. Introduction of the proper drawing technique, introduction to shooting and moving, shooting from cover and concealment and finishing up with shooting the challenge course that imcorporates all the skills of the class. The classes are held one Saturday a month they are for 3 hours, we usually run two sessions 9am to noon and 1pm to 4pm. Each session is slotted for only 10 students. I usually book the morning first then start the afternoon. If you have a large group and want to book a entire session please call, it might be possible to arrange for seperate day or time.  815-955-6094 or email Triggerfarm@gmail.comFor the Advanced Class: May 29th, 2018  The cost is $100.00 This class is 4 hours and starts at Noon on Sundays, (This class is limited to 6 stundents per session) Prerequisites for the class is two prior Basic Defensive Pistol classes from TriggerFarm. For this class you will shoot 300 rounds, the same holster and magazine requirements as the Basic Classs. Topics of instruction will include the basic shooting fundamentals with added malfunction drills. Close quarter shooting (push off drills) shooting from a seated position, Shooting and reloading with weak side hand, drawing , shooting from a vehicle, simulated road rage and car jacking senariors. Shooting the challenge course.

If you’re looking for a 1911 to carry with you every day, look no further than the Springfield Armory® EMP®.
